@node features "Features"

                               Features

-25 boards to play with!

-There's no complex installation: just run the game and play!

-A Top-10 records the best scores and level reached in the game
 and saves them to disk. If no high-score file is present, a new
 file called "Best10" will be created in the directory where the
 game is located.

-Permutax is a "Workbench" game, so it is meant to be played on the
 Workbench screen. The game window can be resized up to a maximum of
 640 x 400 pixels, and the game is redisplayed according to the new
 window size. If the window is too small, it will be automatically
 resized to the smallest displayable size.

-As the game uses as little of the computer's ressources as possible,
 you can run other applications, games, etc. at the same time.

-Permutax works on all Amigas with Workbench 1.3 or higher.

@endnode

@node histo "History"

                               Versions History

  What follows are the various updates that were done since the first
version of this game.

1.0: -First public release.

1.1:  -A Top-10 has been added.

1.11: -Bugfix: Sometimes the game could crash when its window was resized.

1.12: -The pull-down menus have been enhanced.
      -Other minor changes were made to the program code.

1.2: -Many changes were made to the program code:
       -The routine that generates the game window has been revised.
       -Some unneeded program code have been removed.
