       -Some cosmetic changes have been made: the game buttons have been
        redrawn, as well as most of the game tiles.

@endnode

@node play "The game: Installation/Playing"

                             Installation

  The installation is very simple, just place 'Permutax' where you want
on your hard drive, floppy disk, Ram Disk, etc. No other files or
Libraries are needed. The only requirement is that your Workbench must
have 4 colours or more.

                             How to play?

  To play, just click on two tiles, these tiles will swap their
positions. If one or more neighbouring tiles match these tiles, all the
matching tiles will be removed from the board and you will get points
according to the number of tiles that match.

  The scoring, for each set of matching tiles, goes like this:

  2 matching tiles =  1 point
  3 matching tiles =  4 points
  4 matching tiles =  8 points
  5 matching tiles = 16 points

  One important thing to remember: never isolate one or more tiles,
because every isolated tile will make you lose one 'play', and since you
have a total of ten plays, you may need them in order to complete the
game.

  At the end of each level, The game displays the number of moves it took
you to complete that level, the number of isolated tiles, the number of
plays remaining, the score you made on that level and the total score
you made.

  If you run out of plays, the game is over and it restarts to the first
level.

  Have fun!

@endnode

